––– comment –––
Capture the untimed result set as the reference answer.
Keep only numeric ids from the timed query output and drop SHOW WARNINGS noise.
Any id present only in the timed result is a false positive leak.
––– input –––
query='@doc \"AA A28\" NOTNEAR/3 (BB|CC|DD|EE|FF|GG|HH|II|JJ|KK|LL|MM|NN|OO|PP|QQ|RR|SS|TT|UU|VV|WW|XX|YY|ZZ|w1|w2|w3|w4|w5|w6|w7|a1|a2|a3|a4|a5|a6|a7|a8|a9|a10|a11|a12|a85|a86|a87)'
mysql -N -h0 -P9306 -e "select id from test3 where match('$query') order by id asc limit 1000 option threads=1, max_matches=5000, max_query_time=100000;" | sort -n > /tmp/issue-4375-reference.txt
mysql -N -h0 -P9306 -e "select id from test3 where match('$query') order by id asc limit 1000 option threads=1, max_matches=5000, max_query_time=1; show warnings;" > /tmp/issue-4375-timed.raw
grep -E '^[0-9]+$' /tmp/issue-4375-timed.raw | sort -n > /tmp/issue-4375-timed.txt
comm -13 /tmp/issue-4375-reference.txt /tmp/issue-4375-timed.txt > /tmp/issue-4375-leaks.txt
if [ -s /tmp/issue-4375-leaks.txt ]; then echo leaked; cat /tmp/issue-4375-leaks.txt; else echo subset-ok; fi
––– output –––
subset-ok
